--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Things are certainly quieting down. Only 6 new human cases in the
past week though the following report indicates that some cases may
not have reached the central database. I am informed by my colleagues
at ICDDRB (International Centre for Diarrhoeal Disease Research,
Bangladesh) that the successful treatment for their human cutaneous
cases is 500 mg of ciprofloxacin twice a day for 10 days for adults
and the dose for children is 10 mg/kg/dose twice a day, also for 10
days. They have had no deaths. - Mod.MHJ]

[The HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Bangladesh is available at
<http://healthmap.org/r/00Sn>.
A district map can be seen at
<http://photobyfahad.com/fahadnew/images/bangmap.jpg>. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]

